# FluencyLoop is bash. Executable shell and the templates it processes MUST stay LF on every
# platform: a CRLF checkout (Windows `core.autocrlf=true`) puts a stray \r into the shebang and
# into every value read from a file, which breaks the tool under Git Bash / WSL. Pin them to LF.
*.sh          text eol=lf
*.bats        text eol=lf
fluencyloop   text eol=lf
install.sh    text eol=lf
templates/**  text eol=lf
